{"id":26550,"date":"2018-06-20T14:16:05","date_gmt":"2018-06-20T10:16:05","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=26550"},"modified":"2018-06-20T14:16:05","modified_gmt":"2018-06-20T10:16:05","slug":"abu-bakr-on-custody-a-divorced-mother-has-more-right-to-her-children","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/06\/20\/abu-bakr-on-custody-a-divorced-mother-has-more-right-to-her-children\/","title":{"rendered":"Abu Bakr on Custody: A divorced mother has more right to her children"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Al-Qasim ibn Muhammad reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab had married a woman of the Ansar and she gave birth to \u2018Asim ibn Umar, then he divorced her. Umar came to Quba\u2019 and he found his son \u2018Asim playing in the courtyard of the mosque. He took him by the arm and placed him in front of him on his mount. The grandmother of the boy noticed him and argued with him until they were brought before Abu Bakr al-Siddiq, may Allah be pleased with him. Umar said, \u201cHe is my son.\u201d The mother said, \u201cHe is my son.\u201d Abu Bakr said, \u201cLeave him and her together.\u201d Umar did not repeat what he had said.<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Muwat\u0323t\u0323a\u2019 1498<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0633\u0650\u0645 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0645\u064f\u062d\u064e\u0645\u0651\u064e\u062f\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0639\u0650\u0646\u0652\u062f\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064e\u0637\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650 \u0627\u0645\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0629\u064c \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0635\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650 \u0641\u064e\u0648\u064e\u0644\u064e\u062f\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0644\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0635\u0650\u0645\u064e \u0628\u